class Solution:
    def canMeasureWater(self, x: int, y: int, target: int) -> bool:
        def gcd(a: int, b: int) -> int:
            while b:
                a, b = b, a % b
            return a

        if target > x + y:
            return False
        if target == x + y or target == 0:
            return True
        return target % gcd(x, y) == 0

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(min(x, y)))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses the mathematical property that the target amount can be reached if it is a multiple of the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the two jug capacities. It calculates the GCD using the Euclidean algorithm and checks if the target is a multiple of the GCD.
